Below are the '''squads''' for the '''[[1954 FIFA World Cup]]''' final tournament in Switzerland. Each team had to submit a squad of 22 players. All the teams included three goalkeepers, except England, Mexico, Scotland, South Korea, Uruguay and Yugoslavia, who only named two. This was the first World Cup for which the players were assigned [[squad number]]s.

Scotland were the only team to have players from foreign clubs (namely 7 players from English clubs).

